## Log Levels

| Level | Use Case | Example |
|-------|----------|---------|
| DEBUG | Detailed diagnostic info, not for production | Loop iterations, intermediate calculations |
| INFO | Normal operation events | Request processed, job completed |
| WARNING | Unexpected but handled conditions | Fallback used, cache miss |
| ERROR | Failures requiring attention | API failure, validation error |
| CRITICAL | System-threatening failures | Unrecoverable state, data corruption |

### Level Selection Guide

```python
# DEBUG - Development troubleshooting
logger.debug("Processing batch", batch_size=20, items_count=len(items))

# INFO - Business events worth recording
logger.info("Request processed", endpoint="/api/users", status=200, latency_ms=45)

# WARNING - Anomalies handled gracefully
logger.warning("Cache unavailable, using fallback",
               cache_key="user_123", fallback_age_hours=4)

# ERROR - Failures needing investigation
logger.error("External API request failed",
             endpoint="https://api.example.com/data", status=503, retries=3)

# CRITICAL - Immediate action required
logger.critical("Circuit breaker tripped",
                service="payment-gateway", failure_rate=0.45)
```

