### Log Spam Prevention

Use instance-level flags to emit WARNING on first occurrence, DEBUG on subsequent:

```python
class ServiceClient:
    def __init__(self):
        self._fallback_warned = False
    
    def fetch(self, key):
        if not self._primary_available():
            if not self._fallback_warned:
                logger.warning("Primary unavailable, using fallback", key=key)
                self._fallback_warned = True
            else:
                logger.debug("Using fallback", key=key)
            return self._fallback.fetch(key)
```

### Logging API (structlog kwargs)

This project uses structlog configured with standard Python logging processors. Use keyword arguments for structured fields, not %-formatting:

```python
# Correct: structlog keyword args
logger.info("Item processed", item_id="abc_123", status="complete", duration_ms=45)

# Wrong: %-formatting (loses structured data)
logger.info("Item processed: %s status=%s", "abc_123", "complete")
```

